here, each local area (state) decides the law concerning fireworks - in North Carolina, where I am at, the only legal kind are the ones that aren't projectiles, and don't explode (such as sprinklers, etc).  It is also illegal to possess the illegal fireworks (not just use of them) South Carolina, however, does not have this restriction.  As I cross the border I find HUGE fireworks superstores and stands, feeding off the demand from North Carolina. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/em/grin.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
